<p>Microsoft is a multinational technology company founded on April 4, 1975, by Bill Gates and Paul Allen. The company is headquartered in Redmond, Washington, and is known for its software, hardware, and cloud computing products.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p>Microsoft's first major success was the development of MS-DOS, an operating system for personal computers. This led to the development of Windows, which has become one of the most widely used operating systems in the world. The first version of Windows was released in 1985, with significant versions including Windows 95, Windows XP, Windows 7, Windows 10, and Windows 11.</p><p><br /></p><p>Microsoft Office is another key product, offering a suite of productivity applications such as Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook. It was first launched in 1989 and remains widely used across various sectors.</p><p><br /></p><p>Microsoft Azure is the company’s cloud computing platform, offering services such as virtual machines, databases, and AI tools. It is a major player in the cloud computing market, competing with other platforms like Amazon Web Services and Google Cloud.</p><p><br /></p><p>The Surface line of devices, including hybrid tablets and laptops, was introduced in 2012. The Xbox gaming console, first released in 2001, has become a significant part of Microsoft's consumer electronics division.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p>In 2016, Microsoft acquired LinkedIn, a professional networking platform. Other notable acquisitions include Skype in 2011, GitHub in 2018, and Activision Blizzard in 2022.</p><p><br /></p><p>Bill Gates served as CEO until 2000, when Steve Ballmer took over. Satya Nadella became CEO in 2014, focusing on cloud computing and subscription services.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p>Microsoft is known for its corporate culture emphasizing innovation and competition. The company has faced legal and regulatory challenges, including antitrust lawsuits in the late 1990s and early 2000s, related to its Windows operating system and Internet Explorer browser.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p>Microsoft is involved in philanthropic efforts through the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation, which addresses global health, education, and poverty issues. The company is one of the world’s largest technology firms by market capitalization and revenue and continues to focus on cloud computing, AI, and expanding its services and products.</p>
